ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: My use of technology affects my romantic relationship positively.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My use of technology helps me feel more emotionally connected to my partner.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My partner's use of technology affects our romantic relationship positively.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: I feel like I know my partner better because of what I have learned about them through technology.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Technology helps my partner and me make plans for sharing time together.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: When my partner and I are facing conflict, I communicate with my partner through technology more frequently.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Being 'friends' with my partner on Facebook and/or other social networking sites helps to strengthen our emotional connection.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My use of technology helps me feel more sexually connected to my partner. I send flirtatious text messages to my partner.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: If I am feeling anxious about how my partner feels about me, I will check in with them using technology (e.g. texting, e-mailing).
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My partner and I talk in person about how we use technology in our relationship.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Technology helps me to stay connected to my partner when we are not together in the same place.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: When my partner and I are having problems, using technology helps me avoid these problems.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: When my partner and I are together in the same place, it seems like we do not communicate much because we are both distracted by technology.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Using technology helps distract me when I am having problems in my relationship with my partner.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Sometimes, I wish my partner would use technology less to communicate with me.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My partner is demanding in terms of how soon I respond to their text messages, phone calls, and/or e-mails.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: I have felt jealousy as a result of seeing how my partner interacts with others on social networking sites.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: When I am feeling neglected in my romantic relationship, I use technology to seek other companionship.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: I feel like my partner gets distracted by technology when I am trying to talk with them.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: Sometimes, I feel like my partner uses technology to check up on me.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: My partner would say that I get distracted by technology when they are trying to talk with me.
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree

ElementDescription: I have snooped in one or more of my partner's technology accounts or devices (e.g., a phone call log, e-mail account, or social networking site account).
Notes: 1= Strong Disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neutral; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly Agree
